This mod makes all resources discoverable (if they're not already) and adjusts the resources for a variety of states which I feel are egregiously overlooked and/or misrepresented on the map.

For the purposes of this, Lead represents durable, exploitable deposits of early-industrial, electrical, glassmaking, ceramic, or strategic non-ferrous mineral materials that are not otherwise represented by the other resources. Consistent with the logic that appears to have been used elsewhere in the game, this includes: actual Lead, Nickel, Mica, Kaolin, and Quartz/Silica if one of the others is also present.

[img]https://i.imgur.com/Wh5EspM.png[/img]
[h1]States that have been changed by region:[/h1]
[h3]Ethiopia:[/h3]
-> Literally all of them
[h3]East Africa:[/h3]
-> Uganda, Rift Valley, Lindi, Mocambique
[h3]Central Africa:[/h3]
-> Equatoria, all of the Angolas
[h3]South Africa:[/h3]
-> North & South Madagascar
[h3]Indonesia:[/h3]
-> Celebes/Sulawesi, Moluccas, East & West New Guinea, Bougainville

[img]https://i.imgur.com/Qp8JBtZ.png[/img]
This is a pretty safe mod - it's been set up so that any [i]sensibly designed[/i] local flavor mods will easily overwrite conflicts, and it'll dynamically make any super important changes on top.
It has been designed to work with both the Vanilla base game balance, and also with [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3459869359]Explorable Real-World Resources[/url]

[img]https://i.imgur.com/lQRf9dG.png[/img]
[b]Why?[/b]
[i]Because every time I play in these parts of the world I end up fiddling, and this way I'll actually maintain it properly, and hopefully help out some of ya'll.[/i]

[img]https://i.imgur.com/UN80Om5.png[/img]
[h2]Content Credits:[/h2]
[list][*]I referred to Asuna's "Explorable Real-World Resources" and Grawr's "Discover Resources" to sanity check my own changes.
[/list]
[h2]Language Support:[/h2]
[b]There are no localizations in this mod.[/b]

(De Facto) Supported Languages:
English, B.Portuguese(Portuguęs), Simp. Chinese(??), French(Français), German(Deutsch), Japanese(???), Korean(???), Polish(Polski), Russian(??????? ????), Spanish(Espańol), Turkish(Türkçe)

